WEBVTT

00:07.341 --> 00:08.476
[***]

01:01.662 --> 01:02.796
[***]

01:05.866 --> 01:07.268
MARIO:
I'm just sayin'...

01:07.301 --> 01:08.836
I can't believe
that Harris and Bakshi

01:08.869 --> 01:11.272
would be stupid enough
to set foot in the States again.

01:11.305 --> 01:12.640
I mean, why take the chance?

01:12.673 --> 01:14.375
They're gonna be
permanent residents

01:14.408 --> 01:15.809
in Jakarta or Singapore,

01:15.843 --> 01:18.479
or wherever the fuck
they are by now.

01:18.512 --> 01:20.281
Hey, are you gonna eat
those fingers?

01:21.815 --> 01:23.551
Hey.

01:23.584 --> 01:25.419
Sarah?
What?

01:25.453 --> 01:27.555
Your fingers,
are you gonna...

01:27.588 --> 01:29.457
They're called fries.

01:29.490 --> 01:31.592
[MELLOW ROCK SONG
PLAYING ON JUKEBOX]

01:31.625 --> 01:33.194
Look, I hate
to say this, Chief,

01:33.227 --> 01:35.229
but I think we're really
chasing our tails here.

01:35.263 --> 01:36.597
I keep telling you,
they're here.

01:36.630 --> 01:38.432
They're gonna lead us
back to Colin.

01:40.301 --> 01:41.702
Sorry.

01:43.671 --> 01:45.473
You need a break.

01:47.241 --> 01:49.677
I'm fine.

01:49.710 --> 01:50.844
Bill?

01:52.180 --> 01:54.548
[SCREEN BEEPS]

01:57.651 --> 01:59.153
I guess we're leaving.

02:18.239 --> 02:20.341
Cruising speed
back to the precinct.

02:29.283 --> 02:31.819
You know, Sarah,
you're not alone in this.

02:31.852 --> 02:34.622
The massacre affected
the entire department.

02:34.655 --> 02:37.225
Three of the guys were
in my class at the academy.

02:38.792 --> 02:41.629
I wanna find Colin and the guy
that did this too.

02:45.566 --> 02:48.402
[***]

03:03.784 --> 03:05.719
How many was that?

03:07.255 --> 03:09.623
More than two,
less than 10.

03:20.934 --> 03:22.870
Come on.

03:25.806 --> 03:27.341
[SIGHS]

03:29.343 --> 03:30.811
[SIGHS]

03:39.353 --> 03:41.855
I keep telling me
to let it go, but...

03:44.592 --> 03:46.960
every time I close my eyes,
I'm right back there.

03:52.065 --> 03:54.302
In the street.

03:54.335 --> 03:55.869
Hearing the gunshots.

03:59.873 --> 04:01.642
It's like it's happening
all over again.

04:01.675 --> 04:03.411
It's not.

04:05.346 --> 04:06.947
It's over, it's in the past.

04:06.980 --> 04:08.682
Not for me.

04:08.716 --> 04:10.851
Part of me's still there.

04:10.884 --> 04:13.954
Still lying
in a pool of blood.

04:16.524 --> 04:18.258
Waiting for it
to be my turn.

04:25.566 --> 04:27.401
SARAH:
What is that?

04:27.435 --> 04:29.603
Your vacation.

04:29.637 --> 04:31.439
Not into that whole...

04:31.472 --> 04:33.006
virtual
tropical beach thing.

04:33.040 --> 04:36.877
Oh, no?
No, I didn't know that.

04:36.910 --> 04:38.712
No, it's not just
another simulation.

04:39.813 --> 04:40.981
It's another life.

04:41.014 --> 04:42.883
A life?

04:42.916 --> 04:44.918
You know how...

04:44.952 --> 04:47.521
when you're in a dream,
you're still yourself,

04:47.555 --> 04:49.890
but it's not exactly
this version of you?

04:49.923 --> 04:52.326
Sort of.

04:52.360 --> 04:53.927
Well, when you're
in a dream...

04:53.961 --> 04:56.997
you're essentially living
another life, right?

04:57.030 --> 04:58.432
You're in another world,

04:58.466 --> 04:59.667
with another set of rules

04:59.700 --> 05:01.535
that you accept as reality.

05:01.569 --> 05:03.103
That's what this is.

05:03.136 --> 05:05.673
It's another life that you'll
accept as reality,

05:05.706 --> 05:07.975
just as firmly
as you accept this one.

05:08.008 --> 05:10.744
You're not just gonna be
somewhere else...

05:10.778 --> 05:12.713
you're gonna be
someone else.

05:12.746 --> 05:13.914
Who will I be?

05:13.947 --> 05:15.949
I don't know.

05:15.983 --> 05:18.719
Every user's experience
is different.

05:18.752 --> 05:22.490
But it will be someone based on
your own thoughts and dreams,

05:22.523 --> 05:24.425
drawn directly
from your own subconscious.

05:24.458 --> 05:26.827
It's a vacation
from your life.

05:30.898 --> 05:33.634
That does sound pretty
fucking great right about now.

05:38.105 --> 05:39.473
How long is it?

05:39.507 --> 05:41.141
Just a couple hours
to start.

05:41.174 --> 05:42.943
See if you like it.

05:42.976 --> 05:44.912
If you don't, I'll send it
back to development

05:44.945 --> 05:47.781
with a "Dissatisfied
Customer" tag.

05:47.815 --> 05:50.451
I think your head and heart
could use a break from...

05:50.484 --> 05:51.652
being you.

05:51.685 --> 05:53.754
You're too good to me.

05:55.756 --> 05:57.691
I don't deserve you.

06:04.031 --> 06:05.599
Just have a great vacation.

06:05.633 --> 06:06.867
[CHUCKLES]

06:11.104 --> 06:12.440
[DISK BEEPS]

06:14.875 --> 06:17.478
[FLAMES CRACKLING]

06:17.511 --> 06:19.947
[MUFFLED]
George? George?
What are you doing, man?

06:19.980 --> 06:22.483
We gotta move.

06:22.516 --> 06:23.684
[LOUDER]
Come on.

06:23.717 --> 06:25.753
Oh, shit,
you're bleeding, man.

06:25.786 --> 06:26.920
Are you okay? Okay.

06:31.492 --> 06:33.193
I don't know. I don't know.

06:33.226 --> 06:35.062
I can't really
think straight.

06:35.095 --> 06:38.031
You're good, you're good.
Okay, let's go.

06:43.170 --> 06:45.606
Where-- Where are we?

06:45.639 --> 06:47.541
Ha, ha. Very funny, man.
Come on, stay sharp.

07:00.754 --> 07:01.922
All right, here we go.

07:01.955 --> 07:03.624
What the fuck are you doing?

07:03.657 --> 07:05.593
What the fuck are you doing?
MAN: Don't move!

07:08.796 --> 07:09.930
Let's go.

07:10.998 --> 07:12.900
Stay right there.

07:12.933 --> 07:14.067
Move.

07:19.873 --> 07:21.875
You must think
I'm pretty stupid.

07:21.909 --> 07:23.176
Yeah,
we do.

07:23.210 --> 07:24.878
Sorry, what was that?
Well, I do.

07:24.912 --> 07:26.747
COLIN:
I fucking heard you
the first time,

07:26.780 --> 07:28.081
you fucking twat.

07:29.216 --> 07:30.651
What are you doing?

07:33.521 --> 07:35.022
You wanna get his weapon?

07:37.257 --> 07:41.128
Just fucking pull it out,
for fuck's sake.

07:41.161 --> 07:43.597
Hey, George? George?

07:43.631 --> 07:45.032
What are you doing, man?

07:45.065 --> 07:47.568
You thought you'd
just drop in and...

07:47.601 --> 07:48.736
do me in?

07:52.540 --> 07:55.676
[GRUNTING]

07:55.709 --> 07:57.711
All of this was just...

07:58.846 --> 08:00.681
Just avoidable.

08:00.714 --> 08:02.950
Unnecessary.

08:02.983 --> 08:04.985
You just had to do
what I asked.

08:05.018 --> 08:07.087
That's all.

08:07.120 --> 08:08.689
But now...

08:08.722 --> 08:10.190
[YELLS]

08:19.800 --> 08:21.902
You know I, uh...

08:21.935 --> 08:24.171
I once
cut a man's finger off.

08:24.204 --> 08:27.107
And I made his mate eat it
while he watched.

08:27.140 --> 08:29.109
It was disgusting.

08:29.142 --> 08:31.311
But the only thing
that's worse than that

08:31.344 --> 08:35.616
is to cut off his own finger
and make him eat it himself.

08:35.649 --> 08:37.651
What the fuck
is wrong with you?

08:37.685 --> 08:39.653
I'm seeing
if you're hungry, mate.

08:39.687 --> 08:40.888
[GRUNTS]

08:40.921 --> 08:42.089
[ALL GRUNTING]

08:42.122 --> 08:43.557
[***]

08:46.226 --> 08:47.561
[SCREAMS]

08:48.829 --> 08:50.263
[SCREAMING]

08:55.202 --> 08:56.570
Don't move. Don't move.

08:56.604 --> 08:58.572
George,
Colin's getting away.

08:58.606 --> 08:59.773
[GUNSHOT]

08:59.807 --> 09:02.776
Come on. Come on!

09:05.613 --> 09:06.747
[GUNSHOTS]

09:12.152 --> 09:13.320
Fuck!

09:13.353 --> 09:15.623
[TIRES SQUEAL]

09:15.656 --> 09:17.658
We gotta get out of here
before the cops get here.

09:17.691 --> 09:19.026
Come on, George!

09:19.059 --> 09:20.828
Unh!

09:20.861 --> 09:22.996
[BOTH GRUNTING]

09:23.030 --> 09:24.632
Where are we going?

09:24.665 --> 09:25.799
Come on!

09:29.703 --> 09:30.871
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

09:30.904 --> 09:32.906
Okay. Power.

09:32.940 --> 09:34.842
Take us home. Best speed.

09:39.146 --> 09:40.814
George, what are
you doing, man?

09:40.848 --> 09:42.783
I don't know.

09:42.816 --> 09:44.685
I'm still--
Everything's still fuzzy.

09:44.718 --> 09:46.687
M-maybe you should drive.

09:52.392 --> 09:54.327
[ENGINE STARTS]

09:54.361 --> 09:55.929
How did you do that?

10:04.371 --> 10:06.373
How you doing over there,
George? Are you okay?

10:06.406 --> 10:08.909
I don't know.

10:08.942 --> 10:10.410
I'm not sure yet.

10:10.443 --> 10:12.780
You should get that looked at.
Should I call Paula?

10:12.813 --> 10:14.982
Who?

10:15.015 --> 10:17.117
Paula. You know Paula?

10:17.150 --> 10:19.386
You don't remember Paula?
You remember me?

10:22.189 --> 10:24.024
Yeah, you're--
You're Chris.

10:24.057 --> 10:26.860
Chr-- Chris Ginsburg.
We've been friends...

10:26.894 --> 10:28.128
for a long time.

10:28.161 --> 10:29.797
Right. Okay, so I think...

10:29.830 --> 10:31.198
Think you might
have a concussion.

10:31.231 --> 10:32.399
All right, just--

10:32.432 --> 10:34.134
We're gonna get you home.

10:34.167 --> 10:35.769
And I'm gonna call Paula.

10:38.438 --> 10:40.874
PAULA:
It's just
a superficial laceration.

10:40.908 --> 10:42.743
You don't need stitches.

10:42.776 --> 10:44.144
Good.

10:44.177 --> 10:47.881
But chances are
you might have a concussion.

10:47.915 --> 10:49.382
Don't go to bed
for the next six hours,

10:49.416 --> 10:51.819
and stay away
from drugs and alcohol.

10:51.852 --> 10:53.153
You think
you can handle that?

10:53.186 --> 10:55.856
Sure.

10:55.889 --> 10:57.791
I mean it, George.

10:59.092 --> 11:00.694
I heard you.

11:00.728 --> 11:01.995
How's your memory?

11:03.764 --> 11:06.133
[SIGHS]
A bit fuzzy, but it's...

11:06.166 --> 11:07.968
coming back.

11:08.001 --> 11:09.169
What's your name?

11:09.202 --> 11:11.104
George Miller.

11:11.138 --> 11:12.773
Social security?

11:12.806 --> 11:15.943
[SHRILL TONE SOUNDING]

11:15.976 --> 11:18.178
What's your
social security number?

11:24.985 --> 11:27.020
Well, who do you work for?

11:30.290 --> 11:31.959
[MUMBLES INDISTINCTLY]

11:38.198 --> 11:39.332
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

11:41.368 --> 11:44.772
I run Avacom Data Systems.

11:44.805 --> 11:48.475
It's...my company.

11:48.508 --> 11:51.244
I built it in...

11:51.278 --> 11:53.413
2012.

11:53.446 --> 11:54.782
Net worth?

11:56.316 --> 11:59.987
Three, four, uh...

12:00.020 --> 12:01.188
billion.

12:01.221 --> 12:03.356
[SCOFFS]
Close enough.

12:03.390 --> 12:05.058
After all...

12:05.092 --> 12:07.127
what's a billion or two
between friends?

12:12.165 --> 12:13.934
George, do you want me
to stay?

12:19.372 --> 12:21.942
Um, no, I'm-- I'm good.

12:21.975 --> 12:23.443
Thank you.

12:26.546 --> 12:28.481
[***]

12:45.432 --> 12:46.934
[SIGHS]

12:50.370 --> 12:53.340
CHRIS:
Hey, man.

12:53.373 --> 12:56.276
So, uh, the police
found the bodies.

12:56.309 --> 12:58.245
No sign of Colin.

12:58.278 --> 12:59.980
[SCOFFS]
Of course.

13:00.013 --> 13:01.781
Colin...

13:06.153 --> 13:07.921
[SIGHS]

13:09.522 --> 13:11.224
Are you okay?

13:14.094 --> 13:15.829
George?

13:17.630 --> 13:20.600
Uh, listen, I'm gonna go get
Paula back in--

13:20.633 --> 13:23.003
No, no, no.
It's not physical, it's, um...

13:24.537 --> 13:26.874
It's--
It's more mental. I've...

13:28.175 --> 13:30.210
[LAUGHS]
I feel like I wanna cry--

13:30.243 --> 13:32.112
[VOICE CRACKS]
I wanna cry.

13:32.145 --> 13:33.413
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

13:36.249 --> 13:39.853
Uh-huh. I just gotta
pull myself together.

13:39.887 --> 13:41.088
Listen, buddy. Um...

13:43.090 --> 13:46.126
What happened,

13:46.159 --> 13:49.162
it's not gonna be
an easy thing to get over.

13:50.530 --> 13:51.865
[GUNSHOT]

13:55.335 --> 13:57.537
Maybe you need
to get some sleep?

13:57.570 --> 13:59.873
I can't, I can't. Um...

13:59.907 --> 14:02.609
The doctor said I gotta stay up
for the next six hours.

14:02.642 --> 14:05.278
So that's what
I'm doing. I'm-I'm up.

14:05.312 --> 14:07.280
Maybe you need a vacation.

14:07.314 --> 14:09.249
A what?

14:09.282 --> 14:12.452
Well, you know,
the vacation.

14:12.485 --> 14:15.923
"Take a vacation without ever
leaving the house."

14:15.956 --> 14:17.891
That's still
the terrible ad copy

14:17.925 --> 14:19.559
that you're gonna use.

14:26.299 --> 14:28.268
My question is,
when do I get to try it?

14:28.301 --> 14:30.637
I mean, I know
it's a prototype, but...

14:30.670 --> 14:32.372
I could use a vacation too.

14:33.640 --> 14:36.043
This wouldn't work for you.

14:36.076 --> 14:39.913
Each headset
has an individual...

14:39.947 --> 14:41.548
neuronic pulse map that is

14:41.581 --> 14:45.118
uniquely designed for their
prefrontal cortex.

14:45.152 --> 14:47.187
All you would see
is a white light.

14:51.391 --> 14:52.625
I've said this before.

14:52.659 --> 14:54.995
Yup. Your sales pitch.

14:55.028 --> 14:56.964
Hey.

14:56.997 --> 14:59.632
Thank you, Chris.

14:59.666 --> 15:01.568
Really appreciate
that today.

15:01.601 --> 15:03.503
You got it, jefe.

15:08.641 --> 15:09.977
[BELL DINGS]

15:16.649 --> 15:18.018
[SIGHS]

15:18.051 --> 15:19.987
[***]

15:59.326 --> 16:01.328
[TOUCH SCREEN BEEPS]

16:08.435 --> 16:10.137
[LIVELY ROCK SONG
PLAYING ON JUKEBOX]

16:10.170 --> 16:13.640
Say you're right,
and they never left the State.

16:13.673 --> 16:16.143
Four of the most wanted men
in the northern hemisphere.

16:16.176 --> 16:17.710
* Whoa, oh, oh
You think they're gonna

16:17.744 --> 16:19.079
risk hanging around?

16:20.513 --> 16:22.282
Even Colin hasn't
been seen in Chicago--

16:22.315 --> 16:24.117
Does this food
taste right to you?

16:24.151 --> 16:25.585
* There she stood
What?

16:25.618 --> 16:28.621
Yeah, same crap as always.

16:28.655 --> 16:31.258
Seems flat.

16:31.291 --> 16:32.792
Like it suddenly
has no taste.

16:32.825 --> 16:35.328
Wait, are you
listening to me at all?

16:35.362 --> 16:36.663
* Now baby, maybe
Sorry.

16:36.696 --> 16:39.532
It feels like
I'm somewhere else still.

16:39.566 --> 16:42.569
You mean like on vacation?

16:42.602 --> 16:45.538
Wow, that must have
really been something.

16:45.572 --> 16:48.275
Never seen you
this distracted.

16:48.308 --> 16:50.577
It was different.

16:50.610 --> 16:52.345
Gonna eat those fingers?

16:52.379 --> 16:54.347
Okay, fries.

16:54.381 --> 16:56.283
Different how?

16:56.316 --> 16:58.451
* All right now, baby

16:58.485 --> 17:00.720
Like, a coherent dream.

17:00.753 --> 17:02.655
* It's all right now

17:02.689 --> 17:04.357
Stable. Rational.

17:04.391 --> 17:05.825
* All right now, baby

17:05.858 --> 17:09.229
The longer I was there,
the more familiar it became.

17:09.262 --> 17:10.630
* It's all right now

17:10.663 --> 17:13.666
I remembered it,
I remembered my life there.

17:13.700 --> 17:16.803
That's the eerie part,
like...

17:16.836 --> 17:19.139
I was remembering my real
life for the first time.

17:20.573 --> 17:23.610
"A vacation from your life."

17:23.643 --> 17:26.279
Ha. They're gonna
make a fortune.

17:26.313 --> 17:28.515
So does Katie have a piece
of the profits or what?

17:29.716 --> 17:31.584
[DEVICE BEEPING]

17:31.618 --> 17:35.722
* What's your game, baby?
Are you trying... *

17:35.755 --> 17:37.357
Oh, shit, I'll be damned.

17:37.390 --> 17:38.691
What?

17:38.725 --> 17:40.460
You were right.

17:40.493 --> 17:42.529
They never left Chicago.

17:42.562 --> 17:46.299
Dumb fucks got picked up
on an FBI surveillance scan.

17:46.333 --> 17:47.834
Looks like they're
setting a meeting.

17:47.867 --> 17:49.602
Yeah, setting up a meeting
for tonight.

17:49.636 --> 17:51.204
It's beautiful.

17:51.238 --> 17:54.707
Beautiful. I know exactly
where this place is.

17:54.741 --> 17:56.309
* All right now, baby

17:56.343 --> 17:57.510
What?

17:57.544 --> 17:59.246
[***]

17:59.279 --> 18:01.848
It's just so easy.

18:01.881 --> 18:03.850
They're just falling
right into our laps.

18:03.883 --> 18:05.252
I'm not complaining.

18:05.285 --> 18:07.187
Come on, Sarah, come on.

18:07.220 --> 18:08.755
Right.

18:08.788 --> 18:10.723
[***]

18:24.337 --> 18:25.638
I know this place.

18:43.890 --> 18:45.758
[OBJECT THUDS]

18:50.630 --> 18:52.365
HARRIS:
He's late.

18:52.399 --> 18:54.234
How come he's late, huh?
He's never late.

18:54.267 --> 18:57.270
BAKSHI:
Shut up and wait. He'll be here.

19:03.310 --> 19:05.645
Well, we've got a lot to discuss
before the next job.

19:05.678 --> 19:07.914
BAKSHI:
Next job? What the fuck are
you talking about?

19:07.947 --> 19:09.682
The people I represent
would like

19:09.716 --> 19:12.285
to make an even bigger
statement this time.

19:12.319 --> 19:14.921
Something guaranteed to rock
the political foundations

19:14.954 --> 19:17.524
of the entire city.

19:17.557 --> 19:19.659
HARRIS:
What do you have in mind?

19:19.692 --> 19:22.262
Burning down
City Hall?

19:22.295 --> 19:24.697
COLIN:
Try, nuking City Hall.

19:24.731 --> 19:26.433
BAKSHI:
Shit. You're serious.

19:28.701 --> 19:30.470
I'm calling for backup.

19:30.503 --> 19:32.805
We should discuss this
in here.

19:32.839 --> 19:34.407
Please.

19:36.609 --> 19:38.478
[DEVICE BEEPS]
Can't get a signal.

19:39.979 --> 19:41.948
You keep an eye on them.
I'll be right back.

19:43.950 --> 19:46.185
[***]

19:54.827 --> 19:56.729
[BOTH GRUNTING]

20:09.041 --> 20:10.477
Unh.

20:10.510 --> 20:11.778
[PARALYZER DEVICE CRACKLES]

20:20.320 --> 20:21.721
[GRUNTS]

20:21.754 --> 20:23.256
WOMAN:
Mr. Miller?

20:23.290 --> 20:24.657
Mr. Miller?

20:26.459 --> 20:27.627
George, hey.

20:27.660 --> 20:28.995
Somebody call 911!

20:29.028 --> 20:30.763
No, I'm-I'm okay.

20:30.797 --> 20:32.765
I just need some water.

20:32.799 --> 20:35.602
[SIGHS]
Mm.

20:35.635 --> 20:37.003
Breathe, pal, breathe.

20:39.972 --> 20:41.974
Listen, uh,
we should cancel.

20:42.008 --> 20:43.910
You don't cancel
on the Justice Department.

20:43.943 --> 20:46.479
Well, we could say he had
a heart attack or...

